I am currently missing any calls to vkCmdBindPipeline. How do I incorporate this into the code?

To incorporate the vkCmdBindPipeline call into your code, you need to create a pipeline object first if you haven't already done so. You can create a Graphics Pipeline, which will handle the entire graphics rendering process from input assembly to output merger. Here's a basic outline of how to create a Graphics Pipeline and bind it using vkCmdBindPipeline.

Step 1: Create Pipeline Layout

Before creating a Graphics Pipeline, you need to create a Pipeline Layout, which describes the layout of descriptor sets and push constants used by the pipeline:

```cpp
// Assuming you have already created a descriptor set layout called "descriptorSetLayout"
VkPipelineLayout pipelineLayout;
VkPipelineLayoutCreateInfo pipelineLayoutInfo{};
pipelineLayoutInfo.sType = VK_STRUCTURE_TYPE_PIPELINE_LAYOUT_CREATE_INFO;
pipelineLayoutInfo.setLayoutCount = 1;
pipelineLayoutInfo.pSetLayouts = &descriptorSetLayout;
pipelineLayoutInfo.pushConstantRangeCount = 0; // Optional

if (vkCreatePipelineLayout(device, &pipelineLayoutInfo, nullptr, &pipelineLayout) != VK_SUCCESS) {
    throw std::runtime_error("Failed to create pipeline layout!");
}
```

Step 2: Create Graphics Pipeline

Create a Graphics Pipeline by providing the necessary information like shader stages, input assembly, viewport & scissors, rasterization, multisampling, depth and stencil testing, color blending, and the pipeline layout you created earlier:

```cpp
// Fill out VkGraphicsPipelineCreateInfo struct using your own configurations
VkGraphicsPipelineCreateInfo pipelineInfo{};
pipelineInfo.sType = VK_STRUCTURE_TYPE_GRAPHICS_PIPELINE_CREATE_INFO;
// Fill out the necessary fields like stages, vertexInputState, inputAssemblyState, etc.
pipelineInfo.layout = pipelineLayout;
pipelineInfo.renderPass = renderPass;
pipelineInfo.subpass = 0;

VkPipeline graphicsPipeline;
if (vkCreateGraphicsPipelines(device, VK_NULL_HANDLE, 1, &pipelineInfo, nullptr, &graphicsPipeline) != VK_SUCCESS) {
    throw std::runtime_error("Failed to create graphics pipeline!");
}
```

Don't forget to destroy the created Pipeline and Pipeline Layout properly during cleanup:

```cpp
vkDestroyPipeline(device, graphicsPipeline, nullptr);
vkDestroyPipelineLayout(device, pipelineLayout, nullptr);
```

Step 3: Bind the Graphics Pipeline using vkCmdBindPipeline

Now you can bind the created Graphics Pipeline using vkCmdBindPipeline within the Render() function:

```cpp
void GameObject::Render(Renderer& renderer, const Camera& camera)
{
    // ...
    // (your existing rendering code)
    // ...

    // Before calling vkCmdDrawIndexed(), bind the graphicsPipeline.
    vkCmdBindPipeline(*renderer.GetCurrentCommandBuffer(), VK_PIPELINE_BIND_POINT_GRAPHICS, graphicsPipeline);

    // Call vkCmdDrawIndexed()
